  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Regarding ארמה, calliditas, in a good sense, vid., at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 1:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; regarding פּתאים, those who are easily susceptible of good or bad, according to the influence that is brought to bear upon them, vid., also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 1:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and regarding כּסילים, the intellectually heavy, dull persons in whom the flesh burdens the mind, vid., at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 1:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". לב is parallel with ערמה, for the heart (according to its Semitic etymon, that which remains fast, like a kernel, the central-point) is used for the understanding of which it is the seat (Psychol. p. 249), or heartedness  equals  intelligence (cf. חסר־לב, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 6:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "  equals  ἄνους or ἄλογος). We take ערמה and לב as objective, as we have translated: that which is in both, and in which they consist. Thus הבּין, which is a favourite word with this author, has both times the simple transitive meaning of the gain of understanding into the nature and worth of both; and we neither need to interpret the second הבינוּ in the double transitive meaning, \"to bring to understanding,\" nor, with Hitzig, to change in into הכינוּ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(Note: Vid., the Hebr. Zeitschrift, החלוץ, 1856, p. 112.) direct, i.e., applicate.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
